   "source": [
    "# Solar Imbalance Physics-ML — Cloud-Ramp Risk Forecasting\n",
    "\n",
    "**Goal:** Forecast solar PV output and translate forecast errors into imbalance-risk exposure.\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is self-contained for Google Colab. It compares:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Baseline persistence**: assumes future PV equals current PV.\n",
    "2. **Standard ML**: Random Forest with weather/time/lag features.\n",
    "3. **Physics-informed ML**: Standard ML plus solar-position, clear-sky and ramp proxy features.\n",
    "\n",
    "It includes two horizons:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **15-minute ahead forecast**: near-real-time intraday forecasting, usually dominated by persistence.\n",
    "- **1-hour ahead forecast**: risk-oriented horizon where persistence weakens and weather/physics features can matter more.\n",
    "\n",
    "It also defines **large negative PV ramps** as risk events and evaluates model performance during those events.\n",
    "\n",
    "> Transparency note: the imbalance-cost layer is scenario-based, not exact market settlement. It demonstrates how forecast error can be translated into financial exposure."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "696f75ac",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
