    "print('Site details:', site_path)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "30225e98",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Read and inspect data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "40f22ebf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "generation = pd.read_csv(generation_path)\n",
    "weather = pd.read_csv(weather_path)\n",
    "sites = pd.read_csv(site_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Generation shape:\", generation.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Weather shape:\", weather.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Sites shape:\", sites.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "display(generation.head())\n",
    "display(weather.head())\n",
    "display(sites.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b95da11b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Choose one PV site\n",
    "\n",
    "The dataset contains many sites. For the first version of the project, we select **one representative site**. This keeps the project focused and explainable.\n",
    "\n",
    "The code below selects the site with the most non-missing generation records."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "3c16f073",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "generation['Timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(generation['Timestamp'])\n",
    "weather['Timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(weather['Timestamp'])\n",
    "\n",
    "site_counts = (\n",
    "    generation.dropna(subset=['SolarGeneration'])\n",
    "    .groupby(['CampusKey', 'SiteKey'])['SolarGeneration']\n",
    "    .size()\n",
    "    .reset_index(name='n_records')\n",
    "    .sort_values('n_records', ascending=False)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "display(site_counts.head(10))\n",
    "\n",
    "SELECTED_CAMPUS = int(site_counts.iloc[0]['CampusKey'])\n",
    "SELECTED_SITE = int(site_counts.iloc[0]['SiteKey'])\n",
    "print(f\"Selected CampusKey={SELECTED_CAMPUS}, SiteKey={SELECTED_SITE}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "338e556b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Merge PV generation with weather\n",
    "\n",
    "Weather is campus-level, while PV generation is site-level. We merge on `CampusKey` and `Timestamp`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "9a952820",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "site_generation = generation[\n",
    "    (generation['CampusKey'] == SELECTED_CAMPUS) &\n",
    "    (generation['SiteKey'] == SELECTED_SITE)\n",
    "].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "site_generation = site_generation.sort_values('Timestamp')\n",
    "site_weather = weather[weather['CampusKey'] == SELECTED_CAMPUS].copy().sort_values('Timestamp')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Merge nearest exact timestamp values.\n",
    "df = pd.merge(\n",
    "    site_generation,\n",
    "    site_weather,\n",
    "    on=['CampusKey', 'Timestamp'],\n",
    "    how='inner'\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add site metadata.\n",
    "site_meta = sites[(sites['CampusKey'] == SELECTED_CAMPUS) & (sites['SiteKey'] == SELECTED_SITE)]\n",
    "if len(site_meta) > 0:\n",
    "    lat = float(site_meta.iloc[0]['lat'])\n",
    "    lon = float(site_meta.iloc[0]['Lon'])\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    lat, lon = np.nan, np.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Merged shape:\", df.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Latitude:\", lat, \"Longitude:\", lon)\n",
    "display(df.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6d4f533e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Basic cleaning\n",
    "\n",
    "We remove missing PV output and sort by time. We also keep daytime observations for model training, because nighttime PV output is trivially near zero and can make the model look better than it really is."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "43ce3f41",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = df.sort_values('Timestamp').drop_duplicates(subset=['Timestamp'])\n",
    "df = df.dropna(subset=['SolarGeneration']).copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Basic time features.\n",
    "df['hour'] = df['Timestamp'].dt.hour + df['Timestamp'].dt.minute / 60\n",
    "\n",
    "df['month'] = df['Timestamp'].dt.month\n",
    "df['dayofyear'] = df['Timestamp'].dt.dayofyear\n",
    "\n",
    "df['minute_of_day'] = df['Timestamp'].dt.hour * 60 + df['Timestamp'].dt.minute\n",
    "\n",
    "# Keep daytime for forecasting. You may adjust this.\n",
    "df = df[(df['hour'] >= 6) & (df['hour'] <= 20)].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Interpolate weather gaps if needed.\n",
    "weather_cols = ['ApparentTemperature', 'AirTemperature', 'DewPointTemperature', 'RelativeHumidity', 'WindSpeed', 'WindDirection']\n",
    "for col in weather_cols:\n",
    "    if col in df.columns:\n",
    "        df[col] = df[col].interpolate(limit_direction='both')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(df.shape)\n",
    "display(df[['Timestamp', 'SolarGeneration'] + weather_cols].head())\n",
    "print(df.isna().mean().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6537fccd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Physics-informed proxy features\n",
    "\n",
    "This dataset does not include measured irradiance. To still show physics-informed reasoning, we create **solar-position / clear-sky proxy features** from time and location.\n",
    "\n",
    "These are not a replacement for measured irradiance. They are physically motivated features that help the model understand expected daylight structure.\n",
    "\n",
    "Features created:\n",
    "\n",
    "- solar elevation proxy\n",
    "- clear-sky generation proxy\n",
    "- cloud/attenuation proxy: actual PV divided by clear-sky proxy\n",
    "- ramp rates\n",
    "- lagged PV production"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "30a61c28",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def solar_declination(day_of_year):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Approximate solar declination angle in radians.\"\"\"\n",
    "    return np.radians(23.44) * np.sin(2 * np.pi * (284 + day_of_year) / 365.0)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def solar_elevation_proxy(timestamp_series, latitude_deg):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Approximate solar elevation using latitude, day of year, and local clock time.\n",
    "\n",
    "    This is a simplified approximation, not a precise solar-position engine.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    lat_rad = np.radians(latitude_deg if not np.isnan(latitude_deg) else -35.0)\n",
    "    doy = timestamp_series.dt.dayofyear.values\n",
    "    hour = timestamp_series.dt.hour.values + timestamp_series.dt.minute.values / 60\n",
    "    decl = solar_declination(doy)\n",
    "    hour_angle = np.radians(15 * (hour - 12))\n",
    "    sin_elev = np.sin(lat_rad) * np.sin(decl) + np.cos(lat_rad) * np.cos(decl) * np.cos(hour_angle)\n",
    "    return np.clip(sin_elev, 0, None)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def add_features(data):\n",
    "    out = data.copy().sort_values('Timestamp')\n",
    "    out['solar_elevation_proxy'] = solar_elevation_proxy(out['Timestamp'], lat)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Clear-sky proxy scaled to observed max generation.\n",
    "    max_pv = out['SolarGeneration'].quantile(0.99)\n",
    "    out['clear_sky_pv_proxy'] = out['solar_elevation_proxy'] * max_pv\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Avoid divide by zero.\n",
    "    out['clear_sky_index_proxy'] = out['SolarGeneration'] / out['clear_sky_pv_proxy'].replace(0, np.nan)\n",
    "    out['clear_sky_index_proxy'] = out['clear_sky_index_proxy'].clip(0, 2).fillna(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Cyclical time features.\n",
    "    out['hour_sin'] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * out['minute_of_day'] / 1440)\n",
    "    out['hour_cos'] = np.cos(2 * np.pi * out['minute_of_day'] / 1440)\n",
    "    out['doy_sin'] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * out['dayofyear'] / 365)\n",
    "    out['doy_cos'] = np.cos(2 * np.pi * out['dayofyear'] / 365)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Lag features. 15-minute data means lag_1 ≈ previous 15 minutes.\n",
    "    out['pv_lag_1'] = out['SolarGeneration'].shift(1)\n",
    "    out['pv_lag_2'] = out['SolarGeneration'].shift(2)\n",
    "    out['pv_lag_4'] = out['SolarGeneration'].shift(4)  # ~1 hour if 15-min resolution\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Ramp features.\n",
    "    out['pv_ramp_15m'] = out['SolarGeneration'] - out['pv_lag_1']\n",
    "    out['pv_ramp_30m'] = out['SolarGeneration'] - out['pv_lag_2']\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Weather interactions.\n",
    "    out['humidity_dewpoint_interaction'] = out['RelativeHumidity'] * out['DewPointTemperature']\n",
    "    out['temp_dewpoint_spread'] = out['AirTemperature'] - out['DewPointTemperature']\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Target: next 15-min PV generation.\n",
    "    out['target_pv_t_plus_15m'] = out['SolarGeneration'].shift(-1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return out\n",
    "\n",
    "featured = add_features(df)\n",
    "featured = featured.dropna().copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(featured.shape)\n",
    "display(featured.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fcb0dce3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Define baseline, standard ML and physics-informed ML datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "### Baseline model\n",
    "Uses no training. Prediction is:\n",
    "\n",
    "`PV(t+15 min) = PV(t)`\n",
    "\n",
    "### Standard ML\n",
    "Uses raw weather + current/lagged PV + time features.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Physics-informed ML\n",
    "Uses everything in Standard ML plus physics-derived proxy features."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b17c9ece",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "standard_features = [\n",
    "    'SolarGeneration',\n",
    "    'pv_lag_1', 'pv_lag_2', 'pv_lag_4',\n",
    "    'AirTemperature', 'ApparentTemperature', 'DewPointTemperature',\n",
    "    'RelativeHumidity', 'WindSpeed', 'WindDirection',\n",
    "    'hour_sin', 'hour_cos', 'doy_sin', 'doy_cos'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "physics_features = standard_features + [\n",
    "    'solar_elevation_proxy',\n",
    "    'clear_sky_pv_proxy',\n",
    "    'clear_sky_index_proxy',\n",
    "    'pv_ramp_15m', 'pv_ramp_30m',\n",
    "    'humidity_dewpoint_interaction',\n",
    "    'temp_dewpoint_spread'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "target_col = 'target_pv_t_plus_15m'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Keep only columns that exist.\n",
    "standard_features = [c for c in standard_features if c in featured.columns]\n",
    "physics_features = [c for c in physics_features if c in featured.columns]\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Standard features:', standard_features)\n",
    "print('Physics-informed features:', physics_features)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0819f738",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Time-series train/test split\n",
    "\n",
    "We do **not** shuffle. We train on the past and test on the future.\n",
    "\n",
    "For this analysis, we use the first 80% of observations for training and the final 20% for testing."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "49830e2e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "featured = featured.sort_values('Timestamp').reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "split_idx = int(len(featured) * 0.8)\n",
    "train = featured.iloc[:split_idx].copy()\n",
    "test = featured.iloc[split_idx:].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Train period:', train['Timestamp'].min(), '→', train['Timestamp'].max(), train.shape)\n",
    "print('Test period:', test['Timestamp'].min(), '→', test['Timestamp'].max(), test.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7f16f7f6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Train models"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "51b64c3c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Baseline / persistence forecast.\n",
    "test['pred_baseline'] = test['SolarGeneration']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Standard ML model.\n",
    "standard_model = RandomForestRegressor(\n",
    "    n_estimators=300,\n",
    "    max_depth=12,\n",
    "    min_samples_leaf=3,\n",
    "    random_state=RANDOM_STATE,\n",
    "    n_jobs=-1\n",
    ")\n",
    "standard_model.fit(train[standard_features], train[target_col])\n",
    "test['pred_standard_ml'] = standard_model.predict(test[standard_features])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Physics-informed ML model.\n",
    "physics_model = RandomForestRegressor(\n",
    "    n_estimators=300,\n",
    "    max_depth=12,\n",
    "    min_samples_leaf=3,\n",
    "    random_state=RANDOM_STATE,\n",
    "    n_jobs=-1\n",
    ")\n",
    "physics_model.fit(train[physics_features], train[target_col])\n",
    "test['pred_physics_ml'] = physics_model.predict(test[physics_features])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Prevent negative PV predictions.\n",
    "for col in ['pred_baseline', 'pred_standard_ml', 'pred_physics_ml']:\n",
    "    test[col] = test[col].clip(lower=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Models trained successfully.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d0cbd2f2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. Evaluate forecast accuracy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "617c7bd8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def regression_metrics(y_true, y_pred):\n",
    "    rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred))\n",
    "    mae = mean_absolute_error(y_true, y_pred)\n",
    "    r2 = r2_score(y_true, y_pred)\n",
    "    return {'RMSE': rmse, 'MAE': mae, 'R2': r2}\n",
    "\n",
    "metrics = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Baseline Persistence': regression_metrics(test[target_col], test['pred_baseline']),\n",
    "    'Standard ML': regression_metrics(test[target_col], test['pred_standard_ml']),\n",
    "    'Physics-Informed ML': regression_metrics(test[target_col], test['pred_physics_ml']),\n",
    "}).T\n",
    "\n",
    "metrics['RMSE improvement vs baseline'] = 1 - metrics['RMSE'] / metrics.loc['Baseline Persistence', 'RMSE']\n",
    "metrics['MAE improvement vs baseline'] = 1 - metrics['MAE'] / metrics.loc['Baseline Persistence', 'MAE']\n",
    "\n",
    "display(metrics)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d89835e4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 11. Visualise actual vs predictions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "25862fa5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plot_n = min(300, len(test))\n",
    "plot_df = test.iloc[:plot_n]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "plt.plot(plot_df['Timestamp'], plot_df[target_col], label='Actual PV t+15m')\n",
    "plt.plot(plot_df['Timestamp'], plot_df['pred_baseline'], label='Baseline', alpha=0.8)\n",
    "plt.plot(plot_df['Timestamp'], plot_df['pred_standard_ml'], label='Standard ML', alpha=0.8)\n",
    "plt.plot(plot_df['Timestamp'], plot_df['pred_physics_ml'], label='Physics-Informed ML', alpha=0.8)\n",
    "plt.title('15-minute-ahead PV forecast: Actual vs Model Predictions')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Timestamp')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('PV generation')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2ffa3ecd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 12. Feature importance\n",
    "\n",
    "This helps explain what the model is learning. For the physics-informed model, we want to see whether physics-derived variables contribute useful signal."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "0fe44c5a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "importance = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'feature': physics_features,\n",
    "    'importance': physics_model.feature_importances_\n",
    "}).sort_values('importance', ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "display(importance.head(15))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "plt.barh(importance.head(15)['feature'][::-1], importance.head(15)['importance'][::-1])\n",
    "plt.title('Physics-Informed Random Forest: Top Feature Importances')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Importance')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ee59c08b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 13. Estimated imbalance cost layer\n",
    "\n",
    "We now translate forecast error into a commercial risk metric.\n",
    "\n",
    "For each 15-minute interval:\n",
    "\n",
    "`imbalance_volume_MWh = abs(actual - forecast) × 0.25`\n",
    "\n",
    "because 15 minutes = 0.25 hours.\n",
    "\n",
    "Then:\n",
    "\n",
    "`imbalance_cost = imbalance_volume_MWh × price_scenario`\n",
    "\n",
    "This is a **scenario-based estimate**, not exact market settlement."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1157b9d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "INTERVAL_HOURS = 0.25\n",
    "price_scenarios = {\n",
    "    'Low price scenario': 50,      # €/MWh\n",
    "    'Base price scenario': 100,    # €/MWh\n",
    "    'Stress price scenario': 250   # €/MWh\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "prediction_cols = {\n",
    "    'Baseline Persistence': 'pred_baseline',\n",
    "    'Standard ML': 'pred_standard_ml',\n",
    "    'Physics-Informed ML': 'pred_physics_ml'\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "cost_rows = []\n",
    "for scenario_name, price in price_scenarios.items():\n",
    "    for model_name, pred_col in prediction_cols.items():\n",
    "        error_mw = (test[target_col] - test[pred_col]).abs()\n",
    "        imbalance_mwh = error_mw * INTERVAL_HOURS\n",
    "        total_cost = (imbalance_mwh * price).sum()\n",
    "        avg_cost_per_interval = (imbalance_mwh * price).mean()\n",
    "        cost_rows.append({\n",
    "            'Scenario': scenario_name,\n",
    "            'Price_EUR_per_MWh': price,\n",
    "            'Model': model_name,\n",
    "            'Total_Estimated_Cost_EUR': total_cost,\n",
    "            'Average_Cost_Per_Interval_EUR': avg_cost_per_interval\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "cost_summary = pd.DataFrame(cost_rows)\n",
    "display(cost_summary)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "6b5edf4e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Savings vs baseline in each scenario.\n",
    "baseline_costs = cost_summary[cost_summary['Model'] == 'Baseline Persistence'][['Scenario', 'Total_Estimated_Cost_EUR']]\n",
    "baseline_costs = baseline_costs.rename(columns={'Total_Estimated_Cost_EUR': 'Baseline_Cost_EUR'})\n",
    "\n",
    "savings = cost_summary.merge(baseline_costs, on='Scenario')\n",
    "savings['Estimated_Saving_vs_Baseline_EUR'] = savings['Baseline_Cost_EUR'] - savings['Total_Estimated_Cost_EUR']\n",
    "savings['Saving_vs_Baseline_%'] = savings['Estimated_Saving_vs_Baseline_EUR'] / savings['Baseline_Cost_EUR']\n",
    "\n",
    "display(savings)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "e30b2ae6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pivot_cost = cost_summary.pivot(index='Scenario', columns='Model', values='Total_Estimated_Cost_EUR')\n",
    "display(pivot_cost)\n",
    "\n",
    "pivot_cost.plot(kind='bar')\n",
    "plt.title('Estimated Imbalance Cost by Model and Price Scenario')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Estimated cost (€)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Scenario')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=30, ha='right')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
