   "source": [
    "## 15. Project Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "> This project develops a short-term solar PV forecasting framework for imbalance-risk analysis. A baseline persistence model, a standard Random Forest model, and a physics-informed Random Forest model are compared on 15-minute-ahead PV forecasting. The physics-informed model adds solar-position, clear-sky proxy, and ramp-rate features to represent cloud-driven production volatility. Forecast errors are translated into estimated imbalance exposure under scenario-based balancing-price assumptions.\n",
    "\n",
    "Important transparency note:\n",
    "\n",
    "> The operational PV dataset is public and does not include actual plant-level settlement prices. Therefore, imbalance costs are estimated using price scenarios rather than presented as realised market settlement costs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5b396811",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 16. Experiment 2 — 1-hour-ahead PV forecasting\n",
    "\n",
    "The 15-minute horizon is useful for intraday forecasting, but it is naturally dominated by persistence: `PV(t+15m) ≈ PV(t)`.\n",
    "\n",
    "To make the risk/physics angle stronger, we now add a **1-hour-ahead forecast**.\n",
    "\n",
    "Because the data are 15-minute observations:\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "1 hour = 4 × 15-minute steps\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "So the new target is:\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "PV(t+1h) = SolarGeneration.shift(-4)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "This tests whether persistence becomes weaker and physics/weather features become more useful."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "d06e22ec",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create a separate 1-hour target without destroying the original 15-minute experiment.\n",
    "featured_1h = featured.copy().sort_values('Timestamp').reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "HORIZON_STEPS_1H = 4\n",
    "TARGET_1H = 'target_pv_t_plus_1h'\n",
    "RAMP_1H = 'actual_ramp_1h'\n",
    "\n",
    "featured_1h[TARGET_1H] = featured_1h['SolarGeneration'].shift(-HORIZON_STEPS_1H)\n",
    "featured_1h[RAMP_1H] = featured_1h[TARGET_1H] - featured_1h['SolarGeneration']\n",
    "featured_1h['forecast_valid_time_1h'] = featured_1h['Timestamp'] + pd.to_timedelta(60, unit='min')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Drop rows where the 1-hour future target is not available.\n",
    "needed_cols_1h = list(set(standard_features + physics_features + [TARGET_1H, RAMP_1H, 'SolarGeneration']))\n",
    "featured_1h = featured_1h.dropna(subset=needed_cols_1h).copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "split_idx_1h = int(len(featured_1h) * 0.8)\n",
    "train_1h = featured_1h.iloc[:split_idx_1h].copy()\n",
    "test_1h = featured_1h.iloc[split_idx_1h:].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "print('1-hour train period:', train_1h['Timestamp'].min(), '→', train_1h['Timestamp'].max(), train_1h.shape)\n",
    "print('1-hour test period:', test_1h['Timestamp'].min(), '→', test_1h['Timestamp'].max(), test_1h.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "display(test_1h[['Timestamp', 'SolarGeneration', TARGET_1H, RAMP_1H]].head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "64cf3431",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 17. Train 1-hour models\n",
    "\n",
    "We use the same model structure as before:\n",
    "\n",
    "- baseline persistence\n",
    "- standard Random Forest\n",
    "- physics-informed Random Forest\n",
    "\n",
    "The baseline is still:\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "PV(t+1h) = PV(t)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "This is intentionally simple. If the 1-hour forecast is harder, the baseline should weaken relative to ML."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "57b41bd5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Baseline persistence for 1-hour horizon.\n",
    "test_1h['pred_baseline_1h'] = test_1h['SolarGeneration']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Standard ML model for 1-hour horizon.\n",
    "standard_model_1h = RandomForestRegressor(\n",
    "    n_estimators=300,\n",
    "    max_depth=12,\n",
    "    min_samples_leaf=3,\n",
    "    random_state=RANDOM_STATE,\n",
    "    n_jobs=-1\n",
    ")\n",
    "standard_model_1h.fit(train_1h[standard_features], train_1h[TARGET_1H])\n",
    "test_1h['pred_standard_ml_1h'] = standard_model_1h.predict(test_1h[standard_features])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Physics-informed ML model for 1-hour horizon.\n",
    "physics_model_1h = RandomForestRegressor(\n",
    "    n_estimators=300,\n",
    "    max_depth=12,\n",
    "    min_samples_leaf=3,\n",
    "    random_state=RANDOM_STATE,\n",
    "    n_jobs=-1\n",
    ")\n",
    "physics_model_1h.fit(train_1h[physics_features], train_1h[TARGET_1H])\n",
    "test_1h['pred_physics_ml_1h'] = physics_model_1h.predict(test_1h[physics_features])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Prevent negative PV predictions.\n",
    "for col in ['pred_baseline_1h', 'pred_standard_ml_1h', 'pred_physics_ml_1h']:\n",
    "    test_1h[col] = test_1h[col].clip(lower=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Predicted ramps implied by each model.\n",
    "test_1h['ramp_pred_baseline_1h'] = test_1h['pred_baseline_1h'] - test_1h['SolarGeneration']\n",
    "test_1h['ramp_pred_standard_ml_1h'] = test_1h['pred_standard_ml_1h'] - test_1h['SolarGeneration']\n",
    "test_1h['ramp_pred_physics_ml_1h'] = test_1h['pred_physics_ml_1h'] - test_1h['SolarGeneration']\n",
    "\n",
    "print('1-hour models trained successfully.')"
