    "## 26. 1-hour estimated imbalance cost during risk events\n",
    "\n",
    "We now translate 1-hour forecast errors into estimated imbalance exposure.\n",
    "\n",
    "Important distinction:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Forecast horizon** = how far ahead the prediction is made.\n",
    "- **Settlement interval** = the market time block represented by each row.\n",
    "\n",
    "Since the data are 15-minute observations, we still use:\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "interval_hours = 0.25\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "The 1-hour horizon means the trader receives the signal 1 hour earlier, not that the settlement interval is 1 hour."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cf61927f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "INTERVAL_HOURS = 0.25\n",
    "price_scenarios = {\n",
    "    'Low price scenario': 50,\n",
    "    'Base price scenario': 100,\n",
    "    'Stress price scenario': 250\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "prediction_cols_1h = {\n",
    "    'Baseline Persistence': 'pred_baseline_1h',\n",
    "    'Standard ML': 'pred_standard_ml_1h',\n",
    "    'Physics-Informed ML': 'pred_physics_ml_1h'\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "cost_rows_1h = []\n",
    "for scenario_name, price in price_scenarios.items():\n",
    "    for model_name, pred_col in prediction_cols_1h.items():\n",
    "        error_mw = (test_1h[TARGET_1H] - test_1h[pred_col]).abs()\n",
    "        imbalance_mwh = error_mw * INTERVAL_HOURS\n",
    "        total_cost = (imbalance_mwh * price).sum()\n",
    "        risk_cost = (imbalance_mwh[test_1h['risk_event_1h'] == 1] * price).sum()\n",
    "        cost_rows_1h.append({\n",
    "            'Scenario': scenario_name,\n",
    "            'Price_EUR_per_MWh': price,\n",
    "            'Model': model_name,\n",
    "            'Total_Estimated_Cost_EUR': total_cost,\n",
    "            'Risk_Event_Cost_EUR': risk_cost,\n",
    "            'Average_Cost_Per_Interval_EUR': (imbalance_mwh * price).mean()\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "cost_summary_1h = pd.DataFrame(cost_rows_1h)\n",
    "display(cost_summary_1h)\n",
    "\n",
    "base_cost_1h = cost_summary_1h[cost_summary_1h['Scenario'] == 'Base price scenario'].set_index('Model')\n",
    "base_cost_1h[['Total_Estimated_Cost_EUR', 'Risk_Event_Cost_EUR']].plot(kind='bar')\n",
    "plt.title('1-hour Horizon: Estimated Imbalance Cost Under Base Price Scenario')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Estimated cost (€)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Model')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=30, ha='right')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
