   "source": [
    "## 28. Final interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "> The 15-minute forecast is strongly persistence-driven: current PV output explains most of the near-term variation. This is physically intuitive because solar generation usually does not change dramatically within only 15 minutes.\n",
    "\n",
    "> The 1-hour horizon weakens persistence and creates a more meaningful risk-management problem. Large negative 1-hour ramps are treated as high-risk events because they can create imbalance exposure for an intraday energy trading desk.\n",
    "\n",
    "> The value of the physics-informed model should be judged not only by overall RMSE, but by its behaviour during these large negative ramp events, where forecast errors matter most financially.\n",
    "\n",
    "> Physics-informed features are proxy features because measured irradiance is not available in this dataset. They represent physical intuition rather than a full solar-irradiance model.\n",
    "\n",
   ]
